{"lemma":"بِشارَةٌ","slug":"بِشارَةٌ","root":"ب.ش.ر","root_slug":"ب-ش-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ش-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2604","n2605","n2606"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"good news"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"good omen"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the Annunciation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"good news, gospel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"elegance of form or features"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what is pared off of skin"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology 1, noun sense 3, Etymology 1, noun sense 4 are calques of Ancient Greek εὐαγγέλιον (euangélion, “good news, gospel”). Compare Hebrew בְּשׂוֹרָה (b'sorá, “good tidings, good news, gospel”)."},"ipa":["/bi.ʃaː.ra/","/ba.ʃaː.ra/","/bu.ʃaː.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2604","headword_ar":"بَشَارَةٌ","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goodliness; beauty; elegance of form"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"features."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2605","headword_ar":"بُشَارَةٌ","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is pared off from the face of a hide:"},{"kind":"text","text":"what is pared off from its back is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiHoliy^N","text_ar":"تِحْلِيٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aArapN","text_ar":"بِشَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$oraY","text_ar":"بُشْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2606","headword_ar":"بِشَارَةٌ","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aAraAtN","text_ar":"بِشَارَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$aAy^iru","text_ar":"بَشَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$oraY","text_ar":"بُشْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places; and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaA$iyru","text_ar":"تَبَاشِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gift to him who announces a joyful event;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$aArapN","text_ar":"بُشَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, * TA:) or the latter, which is like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumaAlap","text_ar":"عُمَالَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAmil","text_ar":"عَامِل"},{"kind":"text","text":", has this signification; (IAth;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$oraY","text_ar":"بُشْرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aArapN","text_ar":"بِشَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[has the same meaning accord. to common usage, but, properly,] is a subst. in the sense explained above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu$oraY","text_ar":"بُشْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTayotuhu vawobiY bi$aArapF","text_ar":"اَعْطَيْتُهُ ثَوْبِى بِشَارَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him my garment as a reward for the joyful annunciation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA from a trad.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}